Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Gibraltar. The Gibraltarian authorities have introduced regulations and precautionary measures, including restrictions for travellers returning from certain coronavirus affected countries. On 22 March 2020 the Government of Gibraltar announced a total social lock down in Gibraltar to slow the spread of COVID-19. People will allowed to leave their homes only for essential work, to shop for essentials and for brief exercise. Full details of the restrictions which came into effect at 00:00 on Tuesday 24 March 2020 can be found in the Chief Minister’s statement in the Government of Gibraltar Press Release.
The list of at-risk countries covered by the regulations, and full details on travel restrictions is available in the Government of Gibraltar press release. Transit through any of the listed countries is also covered by the regulations.
If you are currently in one of the at-risk countries you should report, as soon as possible, and ahead of your return to Gibraltar, using the email address coronavirus@gha.gi, with the subject line: ‘self-isolation’. You will be contacted by a Public Health professional who will advise you on the best way to protect yourself and others.
All travellers arriving from an at-risk country have a legal duty upon return to Gibraltar to report to a Borders and Coastguard Officer, if arriving by land or air, or an Officer of the Gibraltar Port Authority, if entering by sea. The regulations will be imposed if there is a failure to co-operate.
If you have already returned to Gibraltar from any of the at-risk countries in the last 14 days, even if you do not have coronavirus symptoms, you should immediately:
Call 111 to declare your recent travel
Self-isolate for a minimum of 14 days from the date of your departure
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
